WITBANK - One person was killed and six others were injured when two cars collided on the D686 between Witbank and Ogies in Mpumalanga on Saturday evening, paramedics said. ER24 paramedics attended the scene where they found a 31-year-old man with fatal injuries, ER24 spokesman Werner Vermaak said. "Sadly, there was nothing that they could do for him and he was declared dead on [the] scene. It is understood that he was ejected from the vehicle during the crash." Six people were treated for injuries ranging from minor to moderate. Once treated, they were transported to Witbank General Hospital for further care. The exact circumstances surrounding the collision were not yet known, Vermaak said. African News Agency